<a class='reflink' href='../1.gis/1.2.is.html#theoreminverseiffescommute'>1.2.15</a>
<!-- 1.2.15 -->
<div class="toload theorem">
<p><span class="envidentifier">Theorem 1.2.15
<span style="font-weight:normal;">([<span class='ref' data-tag='MR0466355'></span>, Theorem 5.1.2], [<span class='ref' data-tag='MR1694900'></span>, Theorem 1.1.3])</span></span>
A regular semigroup $S$ is inverse if and only if the elements of $E(S)$ commute. In this case, $E(S)$ is a sub-inverse semigroup of $S$.
</p>
</div>